A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO NATURAL RESOURCES.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 708, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
3 and to read as follows:
4 ”§708- Criminal destruction of a tree on state or county
5 property. (1) A person commits the offense of criminal
6 destruction of a tree on state or county property if, by means
7 other than fire, the person intentionally or knowingly fells,
8 injures, or destroys a tree growing or standing upon state or
9 county property so as to substantially diminish the value of the
10 tree, or substantially damages the potential value of a tree
11 growing or standing upon state or county property, without the
12 consent of the State or county on which the tree stands.
13 (2) Criminal destruction of a tree on state or county
14 property is a misdemeanor.
15 (3) In addition to any penalty prescribed in this chapter,
16 a person found guilty of violating this section shall also be
17 required to pay to the State or county an amount equal to the
